    <briefdescription>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Provides access to the trie storage for runtime API As some calls need an access to a temporary storage (called &apos;ephemeral&apos;) and some introduce changes that need to persist, <ref refid="d7/d99/classsgns_1_1runtime_1_1_trie_storage_provider" kindref="compound">TrieStorageProvider</ref> maintains a &apos;current batch&apos;, which can be either persistent or ephemeral, and provides it for runtime calls </para>
    </detaileddescription>
